This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a novel method to learn a policy from unsupervised demonstrations using supervised learning algorithms. It also involves input estimation, which is a common problem in machine learning. Additionally, the paper could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves learning a policy from data without explicit supervision. The paper could also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY) as it deals with learning control policies. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves processing sequences of outputs.
